This issue is consistently reproducable with Chrome and IE browsers (didn't try with Firefox). 

On Issue Search page, when Advanced filter option is selected, the filter text/form is displayed as a narrow text box instead of expected line. 

See attached screenshot.

As transpired during a [conversation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=293830712&focusedCommentId=420971594#comment-420971594] with [Pawel Niewiadomski|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/~pniewiadomski], JSON-importer currently ignores the "active"-field, when creating a new user: all such users are created as active, even if the field's value is _false_:
        {
            {{"name": "flast",}}
            {{"fullname": "First Last",}}
            *{{"active": false}}*
        }

*+Steps to Reproduce:+*
# Install JIRA 4.4.5;
# Change the Project Key pattern to allow only numbers;
# Create a Project with Key '2013' and create versions for the project;
# Upgrade to JIRA 6.1;
# Try to access the project's versions through the Administration Panel.

*+Expected Behavior:+*
JIRA would display all versions of the project.

*+Actual Behavior:+*
JIRA freezes on 'Loading Versions' and does not display anything else.

*+Workaround:+* https://confluence.atlassian.com/x/dYUXGQ

