Currently, the inline editing feature does not retrieve the latest state of the issue before allowing the user to edit it. 

This could cause some confusion, for if another user has modified it beforehand, the user would not be aware of the changes without refreshing the page, and possibly will overwrite the modifications done by the other user.

It seems that if we perform this via normal editing, when the javascript-layer appears, there is a AJAX-call to get the latest values. Hence, it would be great if the inline editing could also have a call such as this to get the latest state of the issue first before allowing the edit.

